values:
I sort of decided out of pure desire to bitch and moan to devote this live journal to my passion and career in food.&nbsp; So on to the new chapter.

I fucked up at work today.  The truth is I'm still feeling my way around what's the right thing and I fuck up in that regard. But the fuck up isn't very major though it annoyed my chef. Truth was I just didn't think what I was doing was so bad. Thinking back it was obvious, but I just didn't think it through. I went into Friday service with six creme brulees. How stupid was I really.&nbsp; I should have had eight minimum. Naive.&nbsp;

The other thing is that I do get worked up when I get stacked. I look frenzied even though I'm not actually frenzied. I just enter a scramble mode, which does get Kevin, my chef, worried. I don't think I actually lose track of things, I do panic a little but that's just natural stress, the thing is that I'm fighting to catch up and that just how I am in catch up mode. Yes it's stressing but I'm always fighting through, especially when I go into catch up mode. I'm never in a true panic, just a crazy get this, then that done mode. Once again naive.
